Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora of reduced size. Flattened handle. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium, strong red-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.201, 36), now damaged.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1621)
